node.text:
Back in October as part of my partnership with Shoedazzle I announced the Women Of The Future Fund, a $100,000 grant to women in creative industries, and the winners were to be announced this month. I want to thank all of the amazing women who applied for this grant, it takes guts to put yourself out there!! ❤️ I was blown away by how many talented women applied, and I’m so excited to finally share the three winners.

Londyn Douglas: Londyn is a stylist and all around boss!  For many years she has worked with other brands but is now pursuing her dream of running her own women’s vintage fashion brand.  Meeting with her was amazing and I just know she is going to kill it! @londyndouglas 

Gabriella Alleyne: Gabi is a ballerina, aspiring filmmaker and our youngest winner! This girl is so sweet and so passionate about starting her own dance company.  I have no doubt in my mind that she will achieve anything she wants! @gabriellaenpointe

Stephanie Bell: Stephanie is a photographer, video producer and an incredible talent! Reading about her desire to uplift and empower those around her was so moving. Her sense of purpose and drive is truly inspiring and I can’t wait to see what she does next! @bystephaniebell

With women underrepresented in creative industries, we hope this fund serves as a catalyst for change. Though we know this is one small step, we also know these grants will provide life-changing support for those wanting to make the world a more beautiful and equitable place. Congratulations to Londyn, Gabi, and Stephanie!! You’re such an inspiration to us all and should be so proud of all your hard work. It was an honour to meet you all and I’m excited to follow your careers in 2021 and beyond.

#RitaOraxShoeDazzle @shoedazzle

Right now, the future for hundreds of thousands of people who work in live music is uncertain. I’m so honoured to be part of the call on the U.K. Government to protect the venues, festivals and everyone working in the live sector!!❤️

Let’s all show our support to the people that need it by uploading photos from the last show you went to with #LetTheMusicPlay and be heard!!

This footage is from one of my latest shows, a tribute concert for my friend @avicii in 2019 🖤🖤🖤

📸@ronanpark
